Intervals 
--------------------
Distance in pitch between two notes 


Smallest distance between two notes is a semitone
Playing a note, moving up a fret, we have moved up a semitone 
(no open chords)

Two types of intervals :
Semitone 
Tone 

A semitone is an interval of 1 fret. It is also known as a minor 2nd 

A tone is an interval of 2 frets (or 2 semitones). It is also known as a major 2nd 

This is just in reference to guitar . Can be applied to any instrument .
